caption: Update: I retried Wood after two years and was delighted by how much it’s changed. The food was excellent and the staff offered perfect safe service. I’m changing my previous review below as they gave me so such a lovely Experience.  I wood have loved this place if the portions hadn’t been been small or the food hadn’t been disappointing. They served us the saddest looking cheese plate with an inedible cheddar. I let my waiter know and when he said he’d take care of it he actually meant he’d just take 5 dollars off the total cost. The lamb was incredibly fatty and the sea bass dish was a culinary disaster. The fish itself was good but the garnish was bitter and drenched in an acidic bitter broth and the vegetables were inedible.  For a meal that cost us over 100 dollars we were sorely disappointed.
Grabbed drinks at the bar.  Great service and tasty cocktails! A great neighborhood spot.

This is clearly one of the finest place in the area. Anytime I go there I am greatly happy. They keep their high  level service and the topmost level of meals  they offer. You always win with this restaurant. Highly  recommended.
Great local restaurant! The staff are always great and the food is always good. The atmosphere has a great vibe - not to stuffy and not to laid back. Make sure to check them out.
Awesome food quality
One of my favorite places in Chicago. Great staff and truly phenomenal food - try the burger.

Overpriced, underwhelmed. The price tag for most of the food was past it's quality both in flavor and uniqueness. The presentation was nice, but the food itself was OK, not great. For example, their flatbread was very good, but not worth the price tag compared to other places in Chicago with comparable ambiance and food. Their endive salad - lackluster. Their pasta - good flavor overall but not great quality pasta. And their upside down pineapple cake was dry (the sage ice cream with it was good). The service was excellent. All in all, I don't plan to go here again given the dining choices available in Chicago.
Beet salad was out of this world, we had to order two! Cauliflower Pear soup was so creamy and rich. Its a must have! Drinks were good. Staff was very friendly and they follow COVID protocols.

Every time I've visited Wood, I have walked out with incredible experiences. I understand this starts with the company you keep, but we've always been treated so kindly. Cullen coincidentally was our waiter a few times and he was fantastic - charming, kind, and professional. They've made all kinds of accomodations to support covid life and we should pay them in kind. Oh yes, the food - Very tasty! I can vouch for the steak dinner dish, steak tartar appetizer, the chicken dinner dish, and the calamari appetizer! All were great.
Food and wine were average American - "Italian" but truthfully this place could be way less expensive altogether. "Wood" - Not go back. Waiter was great though!
They have stepped up their game in a big way!  Great neighborhood spot.

We love love love this restaurant. Their food is consistently delicious and a little surprising. The bread is always amazing, we can't stop eating the mornay flatbread, and I would strongly recommend any of their desserts. Really, this is a neighborhood gem not to be missed.
Food was so good. And the crowd was so happy.
Good food but pricey, it seems that they’re trying to make up for the covid season. One entree (not real big) and small plate more than 40 bucks.
I can’t believe I haven’t been to this place before! Interesting menu, delicious food, great wine list, friendly and knowledgeable staff. An altogether 5 star experience. Not to be missed.

Great atmosphere, management at the front end was spectacular and hospitable. Food and wine were also delightful. My server however - not the best. I’ve been in the service industry for about 10 years now so I was a little disappointed when our server wouldn’t take our appetizer order until we had decided what we wanted for an entree because the “kitchen likes to have the entire ticket”? Later on in the night I inquired about desserts and he told me to read the menu. Not the service standard I hold myself to, however, the experience was overall good. Will return.
Short rib is 🔥

Don't miss desert! The food here is not only beautifully plated, but also packed with flavor. They have a nice outdoor patio area with heaters to keep you warm on cooler nights, and they allow dogs. Great spot in boys town.
The place has a very Sexy atmosphere. Food is hit or miss but the bartenders are awesome and they pour a stiff drink!
Great meal! Great attention to detail on flavors and blends   Tomahawk ribete was cooked to perfection get it while u can! Definitely going back to try different things!
Great atmosphere. Amazing cocktails. Friendly, competent staff. Delicious food.

Great for cocktails especially whiskey based cocktails, and the male bartenders are 🔥, but the brunch was meh. I ordered corn beef hash. If you love eating chunks of fat covered in oil, this food item from here is for you.

Dinner was pretty good, nice presentation, waiter was on point but everything went crazy when we were in the middle of the dinner, we were sat on the patio tables and some random guy starting acting up rumbustious yelling at the people that were sitting right next to us, it was a very uncomfortable situation that we decided to leave when the crazy guy took a bottle of wine from the table and everything went ruckus, I was like... I'm out of here.
The Smokey Bloody Mary!!!! So Good!!
Such a pleasant and happy experience. I love their sweet corn dumplings.
Acoomodating and friendly.. Food was ok, service great... I had the fish which was tasty but not a very big portion... I'd go back for the service and atmosphere..
The cocktails here are really good! The patio is located on the quiet one-way street side which is nice.
Awesome chef (Devin k)
Great atmosphere and delicious small plates.
the environment is great. Very cozy. Food was bad. We ordered meatball pasta and the meatballs were cold and my friend had diarrhea later.
Delicious drinks and food ! Good service.
Great brunch place in Boystown! Love the name very clever! The staff is amazing specially our server John.
Consistently great food and superior service. Nice outdoor dining space. I recommend Wood.
Great food

I keep trying this restaurant, but keep getting the same results.  The food is meh! You will not leave here talking about how the food was great. You won't talk about it while you are eating. This is better than ok food at a higher end price.  The service is another ugh! Each time I visit this place I feel like I am getting the cold shoulder. I feel automatically judged and I never feel that way. There is some kind of unfriendly environment here the minute you enter the door.  Sadly, there are not too many options in Boystown for food. This would be one of the better ones. However, the food is overpriced. Maybe they have to charge more to pay there rent in this space. I rarely see it busy.  I never recommend this as an option for dinner. Maybe they don't need more business. Maybe I don't understand what they are going for as a vibe.  I wish this place the best, but it is not an enjoyable experience.
Always great food and the sliders right now are very tasty.
The customer service is regularly quick, good vibes, very welcoming employees. I will visit again when I am in town.
Great bar in the heart of boystown. Ideal for date and casual hangout
The quality of food did not match the price point. The octopus was chewy, the monkfish was tough, the veggies were cold, and they didn’t drain the collared greens. We won’t be back.
Amazing food with the friendliest staff. Also,  a great name to boot.
We went here during restaurant week and it was awesome!  Service was really great.  Food was good as well.  Did not disappoint.  We will be back.
Noisy, crowded but good food and friendly service

Everything from service to the food was amazing. The drinks are interesting.  The mousse and bacon are interesting.  The octopus and cavatelli were both beautifully presented. I loved the steak bavette and the duck leg looked good. The dessert was heaven with flecks of gold.  The manager and chef both stopped by to talk during a really busy night for Restaurant Week.
My third time there and normally it's so good. This time it was a miss. Everybody has their off days so maybe it was a fluke.

We went here for brunch and the drinks are definitely strong you only needed one and that saves you in the long run because that warmed you up for the entrees. I became a smoked salmon eater after trying it their on toast, super delicious. Located in boys town and really neat seeing sidewalks rainbow colored.
Really neat stuff! Like, charcuterie? Roasted brussel sprouts? Big deal. Everyone does that. Not like this they don't! I challenge any adventurous diner to fall anything but in love with this menu.

(Translated by Google) An intimate restaurant, attentive staff and very friendly, tasty food ... the steak frites was magic (real home fries and perfectly cooked meat) ... The best restaurant I've done during my vacation Chicago!  (Original) Un restaurant intimiste, un personnel attentionné et très convivial, des plats savoureux... Le steack frites était magique (des vrais frites maisons et une cuisson parfaite de la viande)... Le meilleur restaurant que j'ai fait durant mes vacances à Chicago !
Absolutely delicious, unique food in a modern atmosphere.   Friendly, welcoming staff made it even better.

Ordered food and drinks, food didn’t arrive in over 45 minutes. Many of the staff had asked us about when we would like our food. Friend had to ask aggressively for them to bring the food out after an hour. Staff apologized and then a bartender who wasn’t even helping us at all comes up and says the food was out in 15 minutes. Sorry we didn’t know 15 minutes meant 1 hour. Saw a couple guest seated after receiving their meals and finishing before ours arrived. We watched and heard many of the staff talk about our situation. Extremely uncomfortable situation and not handled with poise. Also they did discount a meal and add it back on the tab. Very tacky, definitely will not recommend.
The caesar salad and Pork schnitzel were amazing.
Good food and drink. Good ambience.
Ok
If you like the new trend of brunch Sunday funday this is super amazing. We also go Friday night to visit Linda the best bartender in Lakeview she bartends in the back. Love this place

During a summertime trip to Chicago, we ended up at Wood while looking for a place to meet a friend for a quick dinner and drinks before an improv show. We were staying in Wrigleyville and, after checking out some reviews, settled on Wood. We were able to get a quick reservation which I liked and were greeted warmly when we arrived. We sat on the patio which is always fun, it's a good people watching spot. Our server was friendly and efficient, the food was pretty good and the drinks were ok. I'd consider dining at Wood again and would recommend it to anyone looking for a good place for some small plates.
Great food and fantastic service, my group definitely enjoyed our time here.

I like the atmosphere of this place. The staff is friendly and the vibe is good. I have eaten here before and have enjoyed the brunch menu. We came in for dinner and had the ribs. I had somewhat expected that they might come on a bed of potatoes, maybe a vegetable as I have seen pictured online. We received a row of ribs which is OK but they are also not cooked long enough, the fat was not rendered off of them making them very fatty and tough.
Several great visits in September, 2019 -- the food, service, and ambiance were terrific.  The food was subtly prepared and delicious.  We are fans!

Post new chef. Burger happy hour special no longer on offer.  Heirloom tomato salad was good. Burger with mushrooms was disappointingly single note of just meat. Needs some acid or Tang to liven it up. Wife loved the cacio Pepe and our friend thought the branzino was very good
(Translated by Google) Good service. Beautiful encounter. Great food. What better ?  (Original) Bon service. Belle rencontre. Bonne bouffe. Quoi de mieux ?

We stopped at Wood today while we were at Market Days. We sat outside, which is very pleasant. Wood keeps a nice ratio of tables to servers - not overloading servers with too many tables like happens at other restaurants. We ordered the chicken Caesar salad and the double cheeseburger, and we shared the two entrees between the two of us. Along with the Pomegranate iced tea, it was another pleasant meal here!
Choices are limited but the food and service was awesome.
Food was ok, service was slow...

Food and the people watching was great, but the service was horrendous. It took 15 minutes for a server to even greet my table last night. I had to fill the waters at the table myself. Not returning back here.

My group of 3 put our name in with the host. We understand that it is a busy weekend, and were told that it would be a 40 minute wait, but we could go to the bar & would be approached when a table was ready. Time went by, tables cleared & we still had yet to be told a table was available. Finally our bartender told us we could have a seat wherever. When we sat down, the host came quickly & told us the kitchen was closed, and that they couldn't handle the traffic. If that was the case, why were we not told at the very beginning when it was busy? We would have been perfectly fine going elsewhere. It is very disappointing that we were set with the expectation that we would be able to eat here, then come to find out after waiting that we were out of luck, & the money we spent on several drinks. The customer service & apology left a lot to be desired.
Great birthday dinner! Nice, knowledgeable staff.

I love a good pork schnitzel, so when I saw it on the menu as a sandwich, I had to have it! The fries were delicious, but the sandwich was a let down. It was too greasy for me, a good schnitzel should not be like that. I’ve eaten here before and have enjoyed the food, and the drinks. The staff are very friendly too. But I was expecting something a little bit better. Also, the presentation seemed weak, maybe add some other color into it.
Most of us had the happy hour food special with the double cheeseburger. It was great!

So amazing!!!!! It was so easy to get a reservation for the time we wanted. Usually I love sitting outside in nice weather, but I didn't mind sitting inside at all this time. The ambiance was great, the waiter was superb, and the food was delicious! I will definitely be coming back here with more friends. Don't forget to try the cheese tasting board ;)
Good food
Great outdoor seating area. Food was so good. Everything was a winner.
Best meal I've had in a long time!!!

We go there all the time for brunch (Saturday and Sunday). They have a small menu but the change it constantly so it is nice to get diferente options though out the year. My husband always gets the classic scramble eggs that comes with cheese and he says that is the best scramble egg dish in the city. I like different things I tried the chilaquiles, the pho, the French scramble,  the cinnamon rolls, the salmon toast.... They were all super good. Mimosas are not that expensive and the play great music!
Pros: Great food and drinks, friendly service, nice location  Cons: Prices are on the higher end
Great food. Great service.
Everything is perfect here. The food itself is just delicious.
The food very good, the atmosphere fun s d stylish, the people personable and smart
Eat here at least once a month and the food and service never disapppint.
One of the best burgers, fun cocktails and friendly staff.
We found this restaurant randomly on Trip Advisor and we're SO glad we went. Great charcuterie and flatbreads and good ambiance and décor
Mother's Day dinner with my son.  Wonderful atmosphere,  great food, and delicious drinks.  Quite busy, but wasn't loud at all.
Great food. Great brunch. Great cocktails. Great spot to hangout with friends and/or family.
Nice place for drinks....great atmosphere
Great fried chix.
Great food & service!
By all means you must try the beef tartare
The food is good but the bar is amazing!
Such a lovely place with delicious food and a wonderful staff
Great space, good beer, bad company. (Bwah-bwah) Looking forward to next time...either solo or with better company! 🙃
Wow, great food and a great atmosphere.
Fun!

Lovely place. Seated quickly (despite its popularity and general businesses), wait time for order was more than 15 minutes, BUT well worth it for the quality preparation, cooking, and presentation put into the meals.
Always delicious!!

Wood is one of few very tasty places to eat in the Boystown area.  They have a nice cheese tray with good jams and breads.   We also enjoyed some of their specialty drinks.   Service was good and each of enjoyed our entrees, especially mine which was the chicken thighs.   I recommend this place highly, especially in the area.

This place has a hamburger that is on par with Au Cheval! It's even better if you factor in that there isn't a long wait like that place. I've had a few other things there but the burger is what really sticks out. The price is good and there's a great selection of drinks. Highly recommend!

Patrick our server was excellent. Our host was attentive & the kitchen with bus staff was like an organized dance of life. Love to belly at the bar with the bartendar but the booth was comfortable. Thanks Wood!
The mushroom cannelloni is exquisite!
The management and staff is great! The food is wonderful and tasty. Limited menu means they do it right.
Wonderful food, drinks, and staff

Long story . Food when finally arrived...then sent back for correction was good .  Management staff initially met responsive to issues like 60 min for steaks to arrive.  Arrived cold . obviously played but not served. Tjey finally came around.  Corrected mistakes.  Treated us better. But was a bit of too little to late.  Food was however very good . Only reason 3 stars  not less

I can’t say enough about this place.  Ambiance, prices, deals, drinks, food. All great and not in that particular order.  The hangar steak was phenomenal. The portions may be a bit on the smaller side, but absolutely must go.

Cute decor, interesting cocktail selection. Seating was very tight. It was so tight that my wife's jacket knocked over the water glass of the next table over. We were excited to eat here, and I was intrigued by the menu. It started off just fine. But then things came off the rails. We ordered appetizers and entrées all at once. Our appetizers came out and were fine. They went heavy on the coarse salt on top of the charcuterie slab. But it was fine. Then, we waited, waited, waited...for an hour and forty minutes for our entrées to arrive. The server came out a couple of times to assure us that they would be out shortly. Then nothing  For an hour and forty. When the entrées finally arrived, I was excited because it must be extremely delicious due to how long they took to make. I got the hangar steak, medium rare. And when I got it, it was cold, and flavorless, aside from the heavy dash of coarse salt, which I had to pick off. And the server, while nice enough, didn't seem to care too much that we waited spent nearly 2.5 hours for a dinner without dessert. Not a tasting menu dinner. Just a casual dinner with friends. All in all, it was a unremarkable dining experience, and with how many great places there are to go to in Chicago, even in the area, I doubt I will be back to Wood.
Good cocktails, and a nice break from the cacophony otherwise rowdy weekend vibe of the area.

The staff was friendly and upbeat, and the interior was aesthetically pleasing. I didn't care for the French toast, as it was deep fried end tasted more like an oily cracker, but the cream that goes with it was delicious. The rest of the food - burgers, smoked salmon inlet, etc was ok, but more so just a more expensive version of what I could make at home.
Amazing food, good service.  Definitely earned its place on the Michelin Bib Gourmand list
Delicious cocktails. Good was great. And cool bartenders!
Always great food and service
Great brunch. Corn beef hash and french omelettes are both amazing.

Wood was better than average but not exceptional.  Honestly I had higher hopes after reading some of the reviews. If you go in thinking "gastropub with a nice bar" rather than "New American fine dining" you'll be OK.  Service was good. Atmosphere was interesting – typical gay bar music which was appropriate for the neighborhood but made it feel more like a bar than restaurant.
Good food... Cocktails less good...
Always a great place to chill.
Amazing!!!
Great cocktails and atmosphere, so so food

It's a very nice place, it's more oriented to relax and take a few drinks on side with some of the good they have there, didnt order something to eat I just wanted a couple of drinks. The barman was really nice and made a couple of suggestions on things I wanted and even made me something not on the menu, i liked and think I'm gonna start being a regular there when I just want to spend a nice night out.

Really friendly and attentive staffs all around! Pretty and neat decor. Went for brunch on a Sunday, didn't have any problem with getting a table for a fairly large party. Everything was good, esp the burger. However, I wouldn't say they were amazing that I can't wait to eat the same thing again. I wouldn't mind trying something else for dinner. I enjoyed my time there.
Always walked past this restaurant and finally stopped by for dinner.  Wasn't really wowed, fun atmosphere, food lacked flavor.
The wonderfully pretentious gay restaurant we have all been waiting for. Hot(and sometimes very sassy) waiters and great food. Good cocktails too. A favorite for me.

Went here for a friend's birthday to have dinner and drinks with a group of 6. The only interesting thing on the menu was the vegan carrot dish, which was good but I was really hoping to have more food options. Giving  stars here for their cocktails - which were really good.
Always fantastic, bustling restaurant. This spot is obviously a favorite for good cocktails, wine, and upscale food.
Great atmosphere
Food and service were great. Scallops and flatbread are fantastic!
Great place. The drinks and good. Seating is a little tight but to be expected.

I attended a group dinner here and the host of said dinner stated that this place was amazing and the new IT place on Halsted Street.  Maybe he overhyped it and my expectations were too high, but Wood did not live up to that great intro.  There was nothing wrong with the service but everything else didn't live up to the hype.  The menu is small so understandably the options are limited.  The food is good, nothing I remember eating stood out.  The prices were obnoxious for the portions with no real star ingredients that commanded the prices being asked.  The drinks were outrageously small compared to the price.  Several drinks were served in the incorrect glasses, but maybe this was on purpose to encourage smaller portions for more money.  Its trendy decor is inviting and it stands out on a busy corner but I could get more from my money at other places in the area and enjoy the entire experience.
Excellent food, especially the flatbread, great service
Great service and food.  Terrific spot for a date or just a casual meal.
Delicious food and atmosphere. Service can be a bit challenging at times.
Nice place! Great people, they are very friendly always smiling and keep asking if you need anything! Drink were good and food was delicious, will definitely go there again.
Great food and atmosphere
Sensational food, service, and atmosphere!
My family enjoy it

Great atmosphere, good cocktails, and decent (but heavy) food. The server, Patrick, was a nice guy but accidentally entered the wrong order in the computer, so the kitchen brought me the wrong dish and I sent it back.  Accidents happen, but what's important is how to deal with them. They brought my meal out when the rest of my friends essentially finished theirs, and I was offered no drink, salad or anything while waiting. Then when the bill came, I was surprised to see that I was charged full price. They basically didn't do a single thing to make up for the mistake or to apologize by offering a dessert...just something. After my initial 2-star review was posted, however, I'd have to say that the manager, Paquale, did handle it well. He found my number from the reservation and called me to personally apologize, to explain that such service was not intended, and offered a gift certificate to give them another try.

Food was great, service was awful. My friend and I went here on a Monday at 8pm. It took over 10 mins for the server to greet us - and the term "greet" is stretch. Then around 15 mins to get our bottle of wine, which came out after the food. At 10 mins I asked about the wine and was told "it's in the works." The manager was also indifferent about our long ticket time - for a bottle of wine that could just be grabbed from the cooler...  When we were finished with our food the server silently dropped off the dessert menu. He barely spoke the entire experience. We seemed like a major inconvenience for him, though if he were simply nice we certainly would've gotten another bottle and probably dessert. It's a shame that a place with decent food has such awful service.
The burrata salad and tagliatelle pasta were delicious as was the burger.
Great value for the food quality. Their chicken is always so tender and delicious, but I don't think I've been disappointed by anything. Cocktails are also always great.
Excellent food, great staff and service. Highly recommend.

When I first walked in I was impressed with the atmosphere and was sure I was going to love this place. Ordered a fried green tomato BLT, really thought it was going to be life changing. Now that I'm done, I'm sadly unimpressed, service was ok, and my BLT was not nearly as good as I had hoped. All in all, still not a bad place, just really didn't meet my expectations.
A spot on caesar salad followed by a scrumptious cheeseburger with perfectly salted fries to match. All enjoyed on they're patio among happy people, including an attentive service team.
The desserts were wonderful

Brunch Chef Carl Sladkey served us phenonomenally and jubiliantly. Keep an eye on this rising gastronomic star. The cinammon buns are to die for, the coffee flows freely, and the ambiance nurtures the soul.
Good food and service 🍸
Rude and bad service. They do not care about their customers at all. Judgemental and racist here. No go!
It's nice.
High prices for portion sizes.  Beautiful space in heart of Not shown.
Delicious small plates in stylish ambiance.
Very interesting. I was unsure about this place so we finally ended up to give it a try. The burger I had was fantastic. Well worth it and a very comfortable atmosphere.

I think the wait staff are friendly enough however they tend to be standoffish. The food has great flavor, however, this is a place where portions will be on the smaller side. The ambience is great though and the layout of the place is good. Overall a good choice, just know what to expect!

I got to wood really excited to try the food. Unfortunately, once we got greeted by the waiter, it went all down hill from there. The waiter had a displeased face as if he was grossed out by us. I don't know if it was because we were Mexican or because we were wearing casual wear (because of the hot weather). Regardless, that should never be the way you present yourself to a table as you're not there to serve who you like, you're there to represent Wood and ensure the customers have a great dinning experience.  Still, I  decided to ignore that and ask the waiter to tell us about the menu. To our surprise, all he could summon was a simple, "the appetizers are one the left and the entres are on the right" in the most condescending tone you can imagine. At that point he asked if we wanted to order drinks to which we said we'd need a minute. As soon as he left I talked to my friends and we all agreed that we were not welcome there by the waiter and I told them we should leave, which we did imediately.  In my personal opinion, I am not willing to stay at a place that cannot make me feel at the very least welcome. I feel like he forgot he's supposed to be working us up for tips, but it's as if he decided he wasn't going to get a good one here (or something like that) so why even bother.  I can say now that I will never go back there again. All that I hope is that others don't experience the same.... In case management is reading this and cares; the waiter was serving the back booth/high stool tables (right behind the host stand) on Monday May 28th at 7pm. He didn't even bother telling us his name.
Fresh ingredients great service... absolutely the best boys town has to offer
Food not exceptional but expensive. Bad service. I would not recommend.
Great cocktails, good service, cool atmosphere, food is great. Always a great choice.
Good service
nice breakfast burger. I think we were there too early as there weren't many people there but the food was good!
Food was inventive and delicious. About $60 pp.
Cool spot for brunch

Great selection of course classic cars cocktails and excellent food. The added side dining area gives you a good selection of seating options and party sizes. Recommend reservations Fri-Sunday. Great place for brunch and day drinking after right in the center of Boystown.

Food was bland as well as I highly believe that I received food poisoning from them. I can't base this off of anything aside from not having eaten anything the entire day except their food and then getting extremely ill the next day. Scallops were cold upon serving, nothing had really any flavor to it.
Great atmosphere.
Hidden treasure!
Amazing cocktails! Split a few appetizers with my pal - scallops and beet salad were great.
Nice decor, great location but not food.  It was 9pm!
Tremendous.
Good food, good service, nice atmosphere all on Christmas Eve.
Earl's Anatomy cocktail is delish.  Truffle spaghetti soooo tasty.  Great cozy and comfortable atmosphere.   Love it!
Go go brunch.  The corn beef hash is the best I've ever had.  The corn beef and potatoes are so perfectly crispy.
Never a bad meal. They keep the drinks interesting to you taste buds.
Always an excellent time. Get the duck!
Good food, good service, cute bartender. Who could ask for more?
Delicious!
Lemon drop martinis are a must!
This place is so cute and warm and intimate. The service was amazing and the food was so delicious. The servers were friendly and kind. I would totally recommend for really any occasion.
Always good food. Decent service. Eat at the bar. It's always a bit more social than sitting at a table and the bartenders are pretty friendly.
Great tasting menu
The best dessert I've had in America. Behold this chocolatey goddess:
Granted this is one of my locals, however their cheeseburger is not to be missed. Solid, consistent kitchen and a good bar to boot.
Very cool!

Was here to attend late night at Wood. The vibe was cute and the music was good, but the service was lacking. Took ages to even get acknowledged at the bar and then even more to be served. On top of that, when one of my friends moved to try and get noticed, he got back talk from the bartender who let him know he had already seen him, but was still not serving him. This place has potential. Hopefully the bartenders will adjust to moving a little quicker and bring a little more customer focused.  Here's a picture of the bar with no one behind it on Halloween weekend night!
Fun little place in the city. Could have a bigger menu, but it's a small place. Food was very good. As were the drinks!
Great spot to eat in Lakeview.
The food was really good just not a fan of those old booth-style seating where if 1 person has to get up the entire table has to as well.
Service is fast! Barely finished my first drink. Beautiful place, lovely people and amazing food. Can't loose. So attentive.

Disappointed in both the food and the cocktails.  Tried their small plates and the two we tried were sadly lacking. The 'spaghetti' was 'pickle-ish' as best described by my dinner companion. In my opinion they went overboard with the lemon or what ever acid they were adding... the pork shoulder, was edible, unlike the spaghetti, however, it was a bit bitter...  I had high hopes, but Overall a disappointing first visit.
Great brunch, good prices, great atmosphere. Each time I've been there it's been easy to get a seat (even outside) during peak brunch hours, and the food has been fantastic. Good mimosas, too.
Creative and limited menu combined with a great wine list make it good choice.
Outstanding!!! Chicken liver mousse and foie gras nom nom nom, must have.
Good food, great drinks and on trend atmosphere.
I has the best company.
Not sure what the fuss is. The build out is nice. Food is just ok. Nothing impressive about the menu.
Great staff, great atmosphere and excellent food.
New age steak house with a limited menu and small portions. Impeccable service and a real good vibe , nice date place.
45 minutes after our reservation we finally had a waiter come to our table. Food was fine, but maitre'd was horrendous
Great food and service
Waiter was a lil pushy
I mean wow. Friendly servers, quick to greet you with coffee and amazing brunch food
Great food and atmosphere!
We went for brunch, it was delicious! You can't beat $5 mimosas that are mostly champagne. The food was really differnt. Nice variety on the menu. The cinnamon rolls are amazing!! Great atmosphere!
The burger was actually amazing
Great staff and good eats
Been here for brunch with friends.  Food and service are great.  Staff friendly and fun.

Our party of four had the mixed board appetizer  which was awesome and we shared four of the small plate and two of the large plate entrees. All were wonderful as we're our cocktails, wine and beer. The Saturday night crowd was a bit loud, so I'd class this as casual fine dining rather than the quieter formal fine dining.
higher end but excellent food and service. Well worth it if you live in the area and are looking for a nice meal out.
Great wines, nice ambiance and definitely yummy food options
We've been three times and the good has never been worth the price. Nice service though.
scallops were great!
Ever changing menu, always a treat with any food. Incredible atmosphere and friendly employees. Always worth a visit.
My family surprised me with a birthday gathering here, and we loved it. We had great service, great food and an awesome time overall.
Great place for brunch, dinner or casual drinks. Docked 1 star because they don't do freshly squeezed orange juice for brunch.
Lovely place, great presentation, awesome food, immaculate service. We've been twice and will be going back again soon.
Been there a few time. Great food and drinks. Bib gourmand
By 1 pm they will be out of every breakfast item..so go for lunch but pass on brunch

Wood came recommended - went before concert at Wrigley.  Service was poor and food came cold 40 minutes after ordering.  When we notified server they essentially took it all to the kitchen and cooked it more.  The food came back looking handled and was severely over cooked.  Manager was nice although not apologetic.  Our sense was they were not at all equipped for a busy evening at all.  Very disappointing- there are many better alternatives if our experience was at all representative.

Very nice place to have brunch and people watch. The atmostphere is very serene yet fun, young and trendy. The food is amazing. I had the Cubano Benedict and the eggs was coocked to perfection, the yolk was perfectly suspended between liquid and not yet solid state. Soft yet supple, gooey yet not runny. Peach belini just wraps up the entire meal.
Fun lively place. Good food and pretty good service.
Cool atmosphere,  good food, great bar.
Super friendly staff. Food is really good. Would recommend.

This is a great place for brunch or drinks. It does take a minute to understand the menu but you'll find once you get passed the "high brow" phrasing most food is comfort food and anything you pick, you will like. The portions are a good size. I will definitely go back.

Fantastic spot!  My friend and I stopped by there last Friday and I am still thinking about the delicious wine and food!  We had dinner at the bar and the bar attenders were on point with wine and food recommendations.  I ordered the Hermanos Mabec and cauliflower entree - it was match made in heaven! :)
The ambiance is cool and classy, and the food and drinks were great too.  We got Fiddler and the Flute which was amazing.
Great food/drink.   Scallops were awesome.  Our waiter....it was either Oury or Corey....couldn't tell....was awesome.

More like 3.5 stars, but I just wasn’t wowed enough by this place to bump it up to 4 stars. Service was pretty good, but my favorite thing about this place is the ambiance, and that’s what bumps it up from a 3 to 3.5 stars. I love the trendy feel of this place, and it seems like a great place to get drinks. But as for dinner, the tables are cramped too closely together, so that if you’re of larger than average size, don’t try squeezing between the tables to sit on the booth side, because you’ll just embarrass yourself. We ordered the lobster spaghetti, which was delicious, but was super tiny, even for a small shared plate. Good amounts of lobster though, which a great white cream sauce. Had to go with the braised short ribs too--- but this dish was somewhat of a let down. The meat wasn’t as flavorful or as tender as I liked. Yes, it was soft and tender, but it still seemed dry at the same time, and just didn’t wow me. Overall, it was more of a bland dish. I wish I was in the mood for a cocktail when I went, but maybe next time, when I’m stopping by just for drinks.

Perfect spot for an undercover date. On a Thursday evening, it was packed and we had to wait a bit for our 8pm reservation, but it was worth it. I loved the Strictly Platonic cocktail (made with ginger beer) and their house ale ain't bad either. The portions are generous and reasonably priced; we ordered 4 small plates and couldn't finish the entree!  I love the burnt orange satin high top booths - it's so cozy in the corner spot! The service was very friendly, and very attentive despite the fact that every table was full. I LOVED the beet salad- it has roasted beets, whipped goat cheese, and a beet mousse that allows you to enjoy different textures of the same flavor. I'm a huge fan of the burrata and tagliatelle, but not so much the sablefish or scallops. Gorgeous presentation-- the chef's training at Alinea is palpable.

The decor inside is beautiful, has a very good lounge type atmosphere. The food was excellent as well. The only knock on this place was the outdoor seating, the tables were a bit wobbly. Other than that, this place is definitely a neighborhood gem.

Went here for dinner on a Friday night.  Atmosphere The atmosphere is great and very inviting. The whole place looks fantastic! Parking is not too bad before 6pm and whether your sitting at the bar or tables - very comfortable and relaxing.  Staff Very friendly and informed! They are really nice and the service was fantastic. Everything came well timed!  Food This is where the place falls apart. The portions were fairly well sized but it lacked many vegetarian options (besides salad and mushrooms). The four of us had the shrimp, mushroom, lox sides and they were ok. Some of the dishes were over salted and didn't really have much excitement to them. I was hoping the sauces would be amazing but it was just ok. For the large dishes our group had the lamb as well as the potbelly (I tried them a little) and they were ok but again it seemed that there was a little too much salt. The lamb was really well cooked and the presentation of the dishes was ok. Overall I didn't feel like there was anything amazing or special - seemed a little lackluster. Their desserts were ok but felt like things I had before - not very inventive but maybe I had different expectations for this place.  Drinks I asked for our waiter to surprise me and he brought out a great drink that we all really enjoyed. He mentioned it was not on the menu.  Please also keep in mind that reservations are required (not sure why considering the place was empty for our time slot for least over an hour). My friends and I went here because they heard about it on WTTW and wanted to give it a try.  Overall I don't think I would come back here for the food - maybe just enjoy drinks with friends at the bar and that's it.

Delicious modern american food. I had the roast venison and shared the charcuterie plate and was extremely happy with both -- my girlfriend had the gnocchi and was blown away by the depth of the rabbit flavors.  The room is beautiful and its quiet enough that you can hear the people you're dining with (a rarity anymore) but still energetic.

A great dining experience from start to finish at this modern American restaurant. Well informed, knowledgeable wait staff who were able to accurately and succinctly answer questions. Small and large plates allow the opportunity for sharing with group or traditional dining. Good wine list. Cozy dining room with good ability to hear and converse with your dining partners.

I have never before written a negative review, but now I have to.  My boyfriend and I went to Wood on a Wednesday night at 8:30 pm.  It was packed (fine), so the host told us it would be a 15 minutes wait, and then didn't ask our name or offer us a place at the bar while we waited.  When we finally found one seat, I squeezed into it and my boyfriend stood.  An hour passed, and no one came with any information.  When we were finally seated, we were told by the waiter that the kitchen was closing in 7 minutes, and we had to order.  I have been a strict vegetarian almost my entire life.  I asked if it was at all possible to make the gnocchi with rabbit confit, sausage, mushrooms, and carrots vegetarian.  Had the waiter said "no", I would have gladly ordered the only (seemingly) vegetarian item on the menu.  He just said "Oh yes, that's fine" and left in a hurried manner.  When my food finally arrived, I was so tired and it was so dark, that I just ate it.  Later, I was awake for most of the night, deathly ill, and then also for most of the next day.  Upon closer inspection of my leftovers and several others' opinions, there was definitely a gelatinous confit of animal fat that was the base of my entire dish.  The only way it was made "vegetarian" was by leaving off the sausage.  I expect a restaurant in a major city in 2013 (practically 2014) to take food restrictions seriously, especially when they can lead to major illnesses (or worse). I have not been so physically or mentally distressed in a long while. Needless to say, I will never return, and will warn anyone I can about this place.

This neuvo American hot spot will prove decadent for any foodie. Excellent menu, wonderful service and great cocktails make for an almost perfect combination in Lakeview. The seasonal menu will delight your taste buds.  The menu is made up of starters, small plates and entrees.  So, if you want to share...great. If you want your own, just as good.  The atmosphere is modern and pristine, but not pretentious. I highly recommend reservations for any meal. This place has already won 2013 & 2014 Michelin Bib Gourmand awards, has been Zagat Rated, and featured on Check Please.  I've consistently bring people here, locals and out-of-towners alike, and ALL of them rave about the food. Simply amazing.  As their web site states, "The proof is in the plates: foodies and casual diners alike will remember his dishes for their exceptional flavor, quality, and execution." I couldn't have said it better.

The four of us went to Wood and absolutely loved it.  The cocktails were good, the small plates (appetizers) were excellent (try the flatbread or cheese tray), and all four of us enjoyed our dinners and ate every last morsel.  Even the dessert menu was awesome.  Our server was cute, and the general lay out of the restaurant was open but intimate at the same time.  Definitely new favorite place to eat.
Great service!
Great place, awesome service and food. A bit pricey but generally worth it.
The food here is delicious.  Great rotating menu and everything we've tried has been great.  Mark is an awesome server.

Fresh and interesting food. Bartenders are awesome and even though it's a little pricy, they have a fabulous beer selection, and delicious cocktails that are a great start to dinner there, or begin, or end a night out.
overpriced
Delicious mixologist cocktails.  Fancy and yummy.  Different from the rest of boyztown.  I took my boyfriend here on our first date. He stuck around.  ;-)
1st date with my boyfriend here.  Perfect spot!  Lots of straight and gay couples on dates.  Delicious scallops. Excellent service!

Been to Wood twice in the last few months. The first time had great food, service, and the cocktails are delicious!!!! I tried a few but I always get the one with the pisco liquor! SO GOOD. I went during the week once and they were a little short staffed so that wasn't as fun but the cocktails are still delish!
This place is awesome.  Love eating at the bar!

This is a great place to visit and eat at the bar.   The small plates taste great and there is great value for the portion size and price.   The craft made drinks are great especially the martinis.   There is a very good wine list, too.   Finally, the staff have been friendly and informative.
